<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-27T16:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-27T16:23:00-05:00" n="883" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d883">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6406.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Nogales</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-27T14:00:00-07:23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1913—2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Rebel forces gathering in eastern Sonora to oppose Huerta Government.
                            Situation of Americans may become serious if railway communication is
                            discontinued.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>